  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A prospective design that studies the effects of a new technique for the treatment of pincer
      nails. The technique consists of a flattening of the bone of the distal phalanx with a
      frontal skin lifting that is performed in patients with a pincer nail deformity. Visual
      Analog Scale (VAS) will be measure before surgery, one month and one year after surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
